Obama Urges Modernization of Food and Drug Watchdog, FT Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-02-25T05:25:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/obama-urges-modernization-of-food-and-drug-watchdog-ft-reports.html
The U.S.  Food and Drug
Administration  needs to be reformed, so it’s better able to deal
with biotechnology and advances in medicine, President  Barack Obama  told a presidential panel on jobs and competitiveness, the
Financial Times reported.  He said he had heard “a lot of commentary” to the effect
that the FDA’s model was “designed for the kind of medical
devices you see in museums,” the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 